listing.name: Any Fields
listing.description:
Quickly build various custom field types and seamlessly apply them across multiple boards. Fields assigned to a board are displayed on each board’s card. Each card can contain its own value for the same field.

Gain the flexibility to seamlessly tailor your Trello environment to fit your organization's unique requirements. Streamline your workflows, optimize your processes, and unlock more productivity advantages by creating custom fields that perfectly match your day-to-day operations.

Any Fields **DOES NOT STORE YOUR DATA** and is securely hosted in Switzerland.

---

### **Take complete control of your Trello data**

Easily create and customize fields with a diverse range of types and values, then seamlessly share those same fields across multiple boards. Take advantage of nested fields to build even more sophisticated data structures.

[Read more…](https://schnapps.tech/products/trello-power-ups/any-fields/field-scope)

![Fields](https://static.schnapps.tech/images/any-fields/any-fields-create-field.gif)

---

### **Unlock advanced reporting with flexible filter options**

The reporting capabilities allow you to search and surface Trello cards based on your custom fields and various card properties. Whether you need to analyze data across a single board or multiple boards, these robust filtering tools empower you to quickly find the information you need to drive strategic decision-making.

[Read more…](https://schnapps.tech/products/trello-power-ups/any-fields/reports)

![Report](https://static.schnapps.tech/images/any-fields/any-fields-report.gif)

---

### **Retain control over access with customizable user permissions**

Any Fields allows you to implement user-level permissions, ensuring only the right people have access to the relevant information. Maintain tight control over your Trello data and workflows, empowering your team to collaborate effectively while preserving the integrity of your critical information.

[Read more…](https://schnapps.tech/products/trello-power-ups/any-fields/settings)

![Settings](https://static.schnapps.tech/images/any-fields/any-fields-settings.gif)

---

### **Documentation**

There is much more to discover with Any Fields - you can save your favorite cards, lock/unlock field saving per card, apply different properties to fields, and even customize the appearance of fields on cards. Check out the documentation and don’t miss any features.

- [Any Fields guide](https://schnapps.tech/products/trello-power-ups/any-fields)
- [FAQ](https://schnapps.tech/products/trello-power-ups/any-fields/faq)
- [Schnapps](https://schnapps.tech)
- [News](https://schnapps.tech/news)
- [Contact](https://schnapps.tech/contact)

---

### **Use cases**

- A prime example of a shared field can be a list of your clients. Create an ENUM field named Client and put all your client names inside. Assign this field to any board you want. Now all your members can set the client on the cards easily by drop-down. In the Reports you can quickly find out which client was used how many times over a specific period.
- What if you have multiple projects for your clients? Create a new ENUM field named Project as a child of Client and specify all the projects for each of your clients. After selecting a client, members can only select projects from that client.
- When you want to prevent accidental changes of the field value, you can set the field as read-only by disabling Editable property. Once the value is stored, it can not be changed anymore.
- Do you want to force members to set the field value? It's easy, just enable Required property. Values won't be stored until all of the required fields are fulfilled.
- A unique combination of the Default value and Editable properties is achieved by assigning a default value to a non-editable field. This makes the field read-only when opening a new card, preventing users from modifying it. For instance, in a scenario with a Client field, users are restricted from changing the client value across all cards on the board.

---

### **Get started for free!**

Enjoy a Free plan to explore all features with limited fields, storage and downloads. If you need more, our tiered pricing is based on your needs, offering two ready-made plans: Plus and Pro, but also a Custom plan for your real needs where you can choose how many fields, downloads, and storage you need.

For further details, please visit Any Fields [Pricing](https://schnapps.tech/products/trello-power-ups/any-fields/pricing).

---

### **Integrate with other Schnapps Power-Ups**

We have developed another great Trello Power-Up **Log Work** that is used to track the time a user has spent on cards. It can be easily integrated with Any Fields by simply installing it on the same Trello board where Any Fields already exists.

[Learn more…](https://schnapps.tech/products/trello-power-ups/log-work)

---

We’d love to hear from you! Share your ideas or questions with us anytime at [support@schnapps.tech](mailto:support@schnapps.tech)

listing.description:
#Track time in Trello cards with one click ⏱️ 

Enable the [TimeCamp time tracking Power-Up](https://www.timecamp.com/integrations/trello-time-tracking/) to gain the ability to track time and generate time reports on any card. Toggle the TimeCamp button on your cards to track time automatically. Most useful for projects that need to gain insights about how much time things take to accomplish. Harvest your timesheet with TimeCamp.

##How to start

- Add the Time Tracker by TimeCamp Power-Up in Trello
- Open the Power-Up settings and choose "Edit Power-Up settings".
- Sign in or sign up to TimeCamp
If you're signing up:
- Register new account
- Authorize the integration
- Select the boards you'd like to allow for tracking
- Choose card and start timer by Power-Up
- Track time with pleasure :)

##How it works

After enabling the Power-Up, the “Track Time” button will be added to your cards. You’ll also get the information about the time recorded for the card by different users. After the first time entry, TimeCamp Time Report will appear in the card.
![TimeCamp Power-Up](https://www.timecamp.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/powerup-trello-timecamp.gif)

##Use TimeCamp for free

You can use the Time Tracker Power-Up for free with the TimeCamp Free Plan. If you need more advanced features like invoicing or custom reports, check our paid plans.

Benefits of Free Plan:
✅ one integration available - use it for Trello :)
✅ unlimited users
✅ unlimited projects and tasks
✅ timesheets

What you get in Paid Plans:
✅ custom reports
✅ invoicing
✅ timesheet approvals
✅ unlimited integrations

Read more on our [pricing](https://www.timecamp.com/pricing/) page.

##Why users ❤️  TimeCamp

_I've been using Timecamp as an extension to Trello and it's made life so much easier. I can track time on a project at the click of a button and stop that timer in the very same way._
Ryan L., Digital Designer

_I use TimeCamp with Trello and it helps tremendously to keep my project on time and under budget. Seeing how long tasks are taking allows constant evaluation and improvement._
Valerian B., Managing Director

_There are a lot of time tracking options out there but TimeCamp provides low friction ways to get the job done. It syncs with a bunch of other project platforms which prevents the need for entering my projects in two systems._
Joel O., Consultant

listing.description:
#Track time in Trello cards with one click ⏱️ 

Enable the [TimeCamp time tracking Power-Up](https://www.timecamp.com/integrations/trello-time-tracking/) to gain the ability to track time and generate time reports on any card. Toggle the TimeCamp button on your cards to track time automatically. Most useful for projects that need to gain insights about how much time things take to accomplish. Harvest your timesheet with TimeCamp.

##How to start

- Add the Time Tracker by TimeCamp Power-Up in Trello
- Open the Power-Up settings and choose "Edit Power-Up settings".
- Sign in or sign up to TimeCamp
If you're signing up:
- Register new account
- Authorize the integration
- Select the boards you'd like to allow for tracking
- Choose card and start timer by Power-Up
- Track time with pleasure :)

##How it works

After enabling the Power-Up, the “Track Time” button will be added to your cards. You’ll also get the information about the time recorded for the card by different users. After the first time entry, TimeCamp Time Report will appear in the card.
![TimeCamp Power-Up](https://www.timecamp.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/powerup-trello-timecamp.gif)

##Use TimeCamp for free

You can use the Time Tracker Power-Up for free with the TimeCamp Free Plan. If you need more advanced features like invoicing or custom reports, check our paid plans.

Benefits of Free Plan:
✅ one integration available - use it for Trello :)
✅ unlimited users
✅ unlimited projects and tasks
✅ timesheets

What you get in Paid Plans:
✅ custom reports
✅ invoicing
✅ timesheet approvals
✅ unlimited integrations

Read more on our [pricing](https://www.timecamp.com/pricing/) page.

##Why users ❤️  TimeCamp

_I've been using Timecamp as an extension to Trello and it's made life so much easier. I can track time on a project at the click of a button and stop that timer in the very same way._
Ryan L., Digital Designer

_I use TimeCamp with Trello and it helps tremendously to keep my project on time and under budget. Seeing how long tasks are taking allows constant evaluation and improvement._
Valerian B., Managing Director

_There are a lot of time tracking options out there but TimeCamp provides low friction ways to get the job done. It syncs with a bunch of other project platforms which prevents the need for entering my projects in two systems._
Joel O., Consultant
